data.description: Owner's pride shows in this beautiful 4 bedroom + 1 non conforming bedroom home with 3 full bathrooms.  One of the reasons sellers chose this home is that it's located in an established neighborhood on a quiet dead end street adjacent to a cul-de-sac.  Seller's have been busy with updates since they purchased the home.  Installed new flooring on upper levels of home in 2022, new hardware and doors 2023, new shiplap in primary bedroom 2023, new ceiling fans with remotes in all bedrooms, new paint throughout home except bathrooms, removed popcorn ceiling throughout except above kitchen sink, new accent wall in dining room, new backdoor and screen door, new recess lighting, new fireplace insert in 2019, new gas furnace in 2022 & extended the driveway in 2020.  You can tell seller's loved this home with the amount of dedication given with the updates.  Other reasons they chose this this home is that all 4 bedrooms are above ground level and are spacious with extra large closets!  The 4th bedroom upstairs has a wrap around closet and another large closet!  They enjoy sitting on the beautiful & large patio watching their children play in the spacious fenced in backyard that over looks a vacant field. They also loved that they can fit an oversized pickup in the extra deep garage with room left over (as shown in pix).  The basement would be perfect for mother-in-law suite because it has another non-conforming bedroom (which has the potential to put an egress window in at a later date to make it a legit 5th bedroom), living area space, full bathroom, kitchenette, storage area and room for furnace, hot water heater & water softener.  The laundry room is in a neutral area off the garage.  Seller's have loved this home since they purchased it and hope you will love it too!
